1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:16,844
[Christmas music]

2
00:00:46,977 --> 00:00:50,119
- [Mom Narrator] Ah Christmas.

3
00:00:50,153 --> 00:00:53,260
Everyone's favorite time of the
year.

4
00:00:54,399 --> 00:00:58,575
Those magical days in December
when anything seems possible.

5
00:01:03,339 --> 00:01:04,409
[alarm ringing]

6
00:01:04,443 --> 00:01:06,928
Except if you happen to be me.

7
00:01:06,963 --> 00:01:07,757
- Give me back my brush.

8
00:01:07,791 --> 00:01:08,585
- It's mine!

9
00:01:08,620 --> 00:01:09,690
- No It's my brush, my brush.

10
00:01:09,724 --> 00:01:12,451
- Guys, guys please, please can
we stop?

11
00:01:12,486 --> 00:01:13,349
[children arguing loudly]

12
00:01:13,383 --> 00:01:14,384
Just give her the brush Anna,
please.

13
00:01:14,419 --> 00:01:17,456
Sophie have you seen my glasses?

14
00:01:17,491 --> 00:01:18,285
- Give it back!

15
00:01:18,319 --> 00:01:20,287
- Guys I said no shouting.

16
00:01:20,321 --> 00:01:23,048
- It's mine, give me back my
brush.

17
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:23,876
- Okay, you're not listening.

18
00:01:23,911 --> 00:01:24,705
Go, kitchen.

19
00:01:24,739 --> 00:01:25,533
[child shrieks]

20
00:01:25,568 --> 00:01:26,362
- [Older Child] Give it back.

21
00:01:26,396 --> 00:01:27,190
- [Younger Child] It's mine.

22
00:01:27,225 --> 00:01:28,743
- It's over there.

23
00:01:30,642 --> 00:01:32,092
- Thank you.

24
00:01:32,126 --> 00:01:34,024
Pancakes in five minutes.

25
00:01:34,059 --> 00:01:34,887
- Quiet!

26
00:01:38,891 --> 00:01:42,136
These last few years,
Christmas seems like another

27
00:01:42,171 --> 00:01:46,313
sugar coated to do on
my already bloated list.

28
00:01:46,347 --> 00:01:49,626
Women everywhere are expected
to conjure their inner Marthas

29
00:01:49,661 --> 00:01:51,594
and do it all.

30
00:01:51,628 --> 00:01:54,769
Mommies / supermodels.

31
00:01:54,804 --> 00:01:55,977
Gourmet chefs.

32
00:01:57,841 --> 00:02:00,603
Of course there's the
decorating.

33
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:03,053
[baby crying]

34
00:02:03,088 --> 00:02:04,779
Doesn't it just make you want
to sing?

35
00:02:04,814 --> 00:02:05,849
[baby crying]

36
00:02:05,884 --> 00:02:07,920
[Mom moaning]

37
00:02:07,955 --> 00:02:10,440
[Mom sighing]

38
00:02:19,242 --> 00:02:21,451
Whoopsie, there we go.

39
00:02:21,486 --> 00:02:22,901
Oh Annie honey, please.

40
00:02:22,935 --> 00:02:24,420
Put on your socks.

41
00:02:24,454 --> 00:02:26,007
- Toes hurt, toes hurt.

42
00:02:26,042 --> 00:02:29,666
- Yeah well nothing is
worse than cold feet.

43
00:02:29,701 --> 00:02:31,703
[puke splattering]

44
00:02:31,737 --> 00:02:34,223
[baby burping]

45
00:02:34,257 --> 00:02:38,434
Except for barf on the Lasky
brief and a 10 year old hooker.

46
00:02:41,816 --> 00:02:44,509
Okay sweet cheeks wash it off.

47
00:02:44,543 --> 00:02:47,339
Is that my heirloom
engagement ring, Nikki?

48
00:02:47,374 --> 00:02:49,099
Give it to me.

49
00:02:49,134 --> 00:02:51,585
- But it's for school.

50
00:02:51,619 --> 00:02:53,380
- Go, wash, now.

51
00:02:53,414 --> 00:02:54,208
- I hate you.

52
00:02:54,243 --> 00:02:55,313
- Santa heard that.

53
00:02:55,347 --> 00:02:57,591
[groaning]

54
00:02:58,419 --> 00:03:00,732
Oh are those yesterday's
clothes?

55
00:03:00,766 --> 00:03:02,975
Please tell me you weren't
up all night working.

56
00:03:03,010 --> 00:03:05,461
- Okay I won't but I was.

57
00:03:05,495 --> 00:03:08,326
You have got to see my new
design for the Community Center.

58
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:13,296
It's, Soph I really think
we've got a shot at this one.

59
00:03:13,331 --> 00:03:14,401
- Hallelujah.

60
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:16,541
- [Dad] Oh thanks.

61
00:03:16,575 --> 00:03:19,199
- It's just that honey, I
think that Nikki needs braces

62
00:03:19,233 --> 00:03:21,546
and my transmission's shot.

63
00:03:21,580 --> 00:03:24,238
You know it would be really
great if you got this job.

64
00:03:24,273 --> 00:03:25,412
[sniffing]

65
00:03:25,446 --> 00:03:27,345
- I know that starting my
own firm has always seemed

66
00:03:27,379 --> 00:03:29,209
kind of speculative to you,

67
00:03:29,243 --> 00:03:31,728
but look I'm a good architect.

68
00:03:32,660 --> 00:03:33,558
I'm good at my job.

69
00:03:33,592 --> 00:03:35,284
I'm going to get work.

70
00:03:35,318 --> 00:03:38,356
- Yeah you have one job, I have
10.

71
00:03:38,390 --> 00:03:39,288
- Excuse me?

72
00:03:39,322 --> 00:03:40,220
- I can't be late.

73
00:03:40,254 --> 00:03:42,256
Go on get your stuff.

74
00:03:42,291 --> 00:03:43,947
Alright you guys I cannot be
late.

75
00:03:43,982 --> 00:03:46,329
Nikki, Anna, come on hurry up.

76
00:03:46,364 --> 00:03:47,744
- Okay listen, you go.

77
00:03:47,779 --> 00:03:49,263
I will take JJ to daycare.

78
00:03:49,298 --> 00:03:51,196
- No, no, no I have him, I have
him.

79
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:52,024
[sighing]

80
00:03:52,059 --> 00:03:53,267
- Soph listen, let me do it.

81
00:03:53,302 --> 00:03:55,476
- No, no, no, I have
everything under control David.

82
00:03:55,511 --> 00:03:56,374
I'm fine.

83
00:03:56,408 --> 00:03:59,204
Girls, now, let's go, go, go!

84
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:00,067
Oh gosh.

85
00:04:01,896 --> 00:04:02,932
- Come on sweetie.

86
00:04:02,966 --> 00:04:04,140
Love you guys.

87
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:08,938
[horn beeping]

88
00:04:08,972 --> 00:04:10,871
[kids arguing and singing]

89
00:04:10,905 --> 00:04:12,286
- Okay.

90
00:04:12,321 --> 00:04:14,944
Anna just stop for a
second please, thank you.

91
00:04:14,978 --> 00:04:16,497
- Can we see Santa after school?

92
00:04:16,532 --> 00:04:17,843
- We're busy later right Mom?

93
00:04:17,878 --> 00:04:19,224
- Oh yeah I'm busy.

94
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:20,467
After lunch I have a staff
meeting.

95
00:04:20,501 --> 00:04:22,158
I have the contracts at two.

96
00:04:22,192 --> 00:04:23,677
I have a deposition at four

97
00:04:23,711 --> 00:04:25,506
and I sure hope that Bob
doesn't expect me

98
00:04:25,541 --> 00:04:27,232
to work late tonight again.

99
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:28,647
- That's all, that's all
you have on your schedule?

100
00:04:28,682 --> 00:04:31,201
- Mom I wanna see Santa.

101
00:04:31,236 --> 00:04:32,927
- Okay girls, we're almost
at the front of the line.

102
00:04:32,962 --> 00:04:33,825
Get ready.

103
00:04:33,859 --> 00:04:35,413
- Why does no one ever listen
to me?

104
00:04:35,447 --> 00:04:36,759
- I can sing for him.

105
00:04:36,793 --> 00:04:39,140
Jingle bell jingle
bell jingle all the way

106
00:04:39,175 --> 00:04:40,107
- Please Anna anything but that
song.

107
00:04:40,141 --> 00:04:43,213
Anything, I can't bear to hear
it again.

108
00:04:43,248 --> 00:04:44,422
Okay.

109
00:04:44,456 --> 00:04:46,320
- I decided I want a puppy from
Santa.

110
00:04:46,355 --> 00:04:48,011
Do you think he'll get me a
puppy?

111
00:04:48,046 --> 00:04:49,668
- Mom, hello?

112
00:04:49,703 --> 00:04:54,397
- Nikki, my first born apple
of my eye, gem of my life.

113
00:04:54,432 --> 00:04:56,572
What is with you today?

114
00:04:56,606 --> 00:04:57,849
Alright, girls, we're here.

115
00:04:57,883 --> 00:04:59,229
Get it together.

116
00:05:00,645 --> 00:05:02,336
Alright girls, come on.

117
00:05:02,371 --> 00:05:04,718
Let's go, go go go.

118
00:05:04,752 --> 00:05:06,444
Good you've got your backpack.

119
00:05:06,478 --> 00:05:07,893
Good go.

120
00:05:07,928 --> 00:05:09,861
Goodbye honey I love you.

121
00:05:09,895 --> 00:05:11,621
I love you, bye.

122
00:05:11,656 --> 00:05:12,484
Bye girls.

123
00:05:14,797 --> 00:05:17,455
[ominous music]

124
00:05:18,870 --> 00:05:22,425
- Sophie Kelly are you avoiding
me?

125
00:05:22,460 --> 00:05:25,359
- Hey neighbor, no of course
not.

126
00:05:25,394 --> 00:05:27,741
- Did you bring your
cookies for the bake sale?

127
00:05:27,775 --> 00:05:29,363
- They're cooling on the rack.

128
00:05:29,398 --> 00:05:31,434
- It's just awesome of you to
volunteer.

129
00:05:31,469 --> 00:05:35,404
I don't know how you do
it, you Superwoman you.

130
00:05:38,510 --> 00:05:39,339
- Yay.

131
00:05:41,375 --> 00:05:43,032
[sighing]

132
00:05:43,066 --> 00:05:44,792
[school bell ringing]

133
00:05:44,827 --> 00:05:47,795
- So your Mom really forgot
about the Christmas play today?

134
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:50,039
- Yeah I even put my
makeup on to remind her.

135
00:05:50,073 --> 00:05:51,178
- And what'd she say?

136
00:05:51,212 --> 00:05:54,284
- She called me a hooker
and then made my Dad upset.

137
00:05:54,319 --> 00:05:55,872
- Whoa.

138
00:05:55,907 --> 00:05:57,253
What's a hooker?

139
00:05:59,428 --> 00:06:02,120
[ominous music]

140
00:06:03,155 --> 00:06:05,399
- They man's a donkey who
says it's my own fault

141
00:06:05,434 --> 00:06:07,539
I signed a contract with no
benefits.

142
00:06:07,574 --> 00:06:09,610
I hope this baby knows how to
file.

143
00:06:09,645 --> 00:06:10,439
- You alright Claire?

144
00:06:10,473 --> 00:06:11,578
- Do I look like a whale?

145
00:06:11,612 --> 00:06:12,406
- No.

146
00:06:12,441 --> 00:06:13,269
- Okay.

147
00:06:13,303 --> 00:06:14,097
- You're beautiful.

148
00:06:14,132 --> 00:06:15,064
Oh my gosh.

149
00:06:18,930 --> 00:06:19,724
- Oh thank Hades.

150
00:06:19,758 --> 00:06:21,898
Bob is choking on his All Bran.

151
00:06:21,933 --> 00:06:23,521
Gosh did I miss the Lasky
meeting?

152
00:06:23,555 --> 00:06:24,625
- They were early.

153
00:06:24,660 --> 00:06:25,937
I swear that woman gets
up at five in the morning

154
00:06:25,971 --> 00:06:28,146
just to sharpen her horns.

155
00:06:28,180 --> 00:06:29,699
Here they come.

156
00:06:29,734 --> 00:06:32,219
- Mark, rest assured this firm--

157
00:06:32,253 --> 00:06:33,116
- Quick, duck!

158
00:06:33,151 --> 00:06:37,327
- Will be at your back and call
24 / 7.

159
00:06:44,956 --> 00:06:47,510
- That man is vile, vile!

160
00:06:47,545 --> 00:06:51,652
- Okay look, I need you
to print me up a new copy

161
00:06:52,515 --> 00:06:55,449
of this contract and send
some cookies to school

162
00:06:55,484 --> 00:06:57,831
and rough them up a bit so they
look like they're home made.

163
00:06:57,865 --> 00:06:59,488
You're an angel, thank you.

164
00:06:59,522 --> 00:07:01,144
- You're my goddess.

165
00:07:01,179 --> 00:07:04,078
Which is why it is with
deep regret that I have to

166
00:07:04,113 --> 00:07:05,321
give you the latest.

167
00:07:05,355 --> 00:07:06,702
- What do you mean you're
going to give the Lasky account

168
00:07:06,736 --> 00:07:07,737
to Chuck?

169
00:07:07,772 --> 00:07:11,016
My work on this file has been
spotless.

170
00:07:11,948 --> 00:07:13,778
Figuratively speaking.

171
00:07:14,986 --> 00:07:19,162
- So when I climbed Everest
last year I had the best guide

172
00:07:20,301 --> 00:07:21,130
in Nepal.

173
00:07:22,511 --> 00:07:26,687
Got caught on the peak, ice
storm, 40 below, lost my pick.

174
00:07:28,206 --> 00:07:29,863
Sherpa saved my ass.

175
00:07:31,554 --> 00:07:35,558
- That's a beautiful story
Bob, what's your point.

176
00:07:35,593 --> 00:07:37,802
- You leave work early
several times a week.

177
00:07:37,836 --> 00:07:39,976
- Yeah well things have
been a little hectic lately.

178
00:07:40,011 --> 00:07:42,462
- Well there's a major
property deal for the firm.

179
00:07:42,496 --> 00:07:44,222
I just don't know if you're
the right person to be

180
00:07:44,256 --> 00:07:46,327
up on that mountain right now.

181
00:07:46,362 --> 00:07:47,605
- Excuse me?

182
00:07:47,639 --> 00:07:50,642
- Well ever since you came
back from your last kid,

183
00:07:50,677 --> 00:07:54,266
and believe me motherhood
is the most important job

184
00:07:54,301 --> 00:07:55,923
in the world.

185
00:07:55,958 --> 00:07:59,409
I just think you may have lost
your edge.

186
00:08:01,791 --> 00:08:03,103
- Lost my edge?

187
00:08:03,137 --> 00:08:03,966
I'm edgy.

188
00:08:05,346 --> 00:08:06,175
No edge.

189
00:08:06,209 --> 00:08:08,453
- We're making that push for
the top.

190
00:08:08,488 --> 00:08:10,904
You gotta be able to
depend on your whole team

191
00:08:10,938 --> 00:08:12,043
to get you there.

192
00:08:12,077 --> 00:08:13,044
- I'm here for you Bob.

193
00:08:13,078 --> 00:08:13,976
Look at me.

194
00:08:16,910 --> 00:08:18,843
Okay I might have a run in my
stockings

195
00:08:18,877 --> 00:08:20,085
but I am here for you.

196
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:21,949
- Oh come on, when push comes
to shove

197
00:08:21,984 --> 00:08:23,537
what's it going to be?

198
00:08:23,572 --> 00:08:27,714
24 / 7 with the Laskys or
little Angela's got pneumonia.

199
00:08:29,647 --> 00:08:33,823
- Her name is Annie and she
refuses to put on warm socks.

200
00:08:35,066 --> 00:08:38,207
- Not all Mommies can
reach the peak Sophie.

201
00:08:38,241 --> 00:08:40,140
- Or the corner office.

202
00:08:41,659 --> 00:08:43,764
- Sophie, Sophie, Sophie.

203
00:08:46,318 --> 00:08:48,217
Come on, time is money.

204
00:08:57,329 --> 00:08:58,434
[knocking]

205
00:08:58,468 --> 00:08:59,987
- Come in.

206
00:09:00,022 --> 00:09:01,506
- Hey sis.

207
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:02,369
- Hi.

208
00:09:04,371 --> 00:09:05,786
Do you ever call first?

209
00:09:05,821 --> 00:09:07,961
- More spontaneous this way.

210
00:09:07,995 --> 00:09:10,826
So did we ever decide what
we were going to get Mom yet?

211
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:13,587
- We were supposed to get
her something last week.

212
00:09:13,622 --> 00:09:15,037
- Is this some sort of passive
aggressive

213
00:09:15,071 --> 00:09:16,348
sibling order thing?

214
00:09:16,383 --> 00:09:18,592
- No, no, no, I'll get
her something tonight.

215
00:09:18,627 --> 00:09:19,662
I've got to go to the mall.

216
00:09:19,697 --> 00:09:20,594
- No, tonight you're
putting on a pretty dress

217
00:09:20,629 --> 00:09:22,769
and making nice with the
clients.

218
00:09:22,803 --> 00:09:24,736
- My god the office party.

219
00:09:24,771 --> 00:09:25,875
- Any single men for me?

220
00:09:25,910 --> 00:09:26,980
- No.

221
00:09:27,014 --> 00:09:28,947
- Just for that I'm going
to bring the mashed yams

222
00:09:28,982 --> 00:09:31,881
with the little colored
marshmallows for Christmas
dinner.

223
00:09:31,916 --> 00:09:34,919
- Oh I forgot I was going to
host that.

224
00:09:34,953 --> 00:09:36,645
I volunteered.

225
00:09:36,679 --> 00:09:38,854
- After she got drunk
drinking two shots of tequila

226
00:09:38,888 --> 00:09:40,752
at Mom and Dad's anniversary
party.

227
00:09:40,787 --> 00:09:42,512
- Not a good day.

228
00:09:42,547 --> 00:09:43,341
- See ya.

229
00:09:43,375 --> 00:09:44,376
- Bye honey.

230
00:09:46,724 --> 00:09:49,416
[sighing]

231
00:09:49,450 --> 00:09:50,935
[metal clanking]

232
00:09:50,969 --> 00:09:53,558
- The chair, I know, I'm on it.

233
00:09:55,905 --> 00:09:57,217
- [Announcer] Attention holiday
shoppers,

234
00:09:57,251 --> 00:09:59,046
there's only four days
left 'til Christmas.

235
00:09:59,081 --> 00:10:01,324
Be sure to stop by our
Santa's Village to get your

236
00:10:01,359 --> 00:10:02,774
photo with Santa.

237
00:10:05,087 --> 00:10:07,537
[upbeat Christmas music]

238
00:10:07,572 --> 00:10:09,125
- [Sophie] Oh baby please.

239
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:10,575
- [Child] I'm going
first, I'm going first.

240
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:11,403
- [Sophie] It's going to be
great.

241
00:10:11,438 --> 00:10:12,612
Everything's going to be fine.

242
00:10:12,646 --> 00:10:15,718
Would you guys stop arguing,
please.

243
00:10:15,753 --> 00:10:18,134
Santa's going to hear you.

244
00:10:18,169 --> 00:10:22,276
Okay just stand quietly
you're almost there.

245
00:10:22,311 --> 00:10:23,588
- [Child] No I'm the one going
first.

246
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:25,038
Mom said I could.

247
00:10:25,072 --> 00:10:25,970
- Hey Dave?

248
00:10:28,455 --> 00:10:29,283
Dave?

249
00:10:30,146 --> 00:10:32,010
Pick up the phone.

250
00:10:32,045 --> 00:10:35,531
My battery's dying Dave,
please pick up the phone.

251
00:10:35,565 --> 00:10:36,808
I'm at the mall.

252
00:10:36,843 --> 00:10:40,191
I'm trying to get a dress and
I need you to take care of--

253
00:10:40,225 --> 00:10:41,537
[squealing]

254
00:10:41,571 --> 00:10:45,714
The kids because I have
this office party tonight.

255
00:10:46,715 --> 00:10:48,302
Pick up the phone.

256
00:10:48,337 --> 00:10:49,821
Honey!

257
00:10:49,856 --> 00:10:52,099
[growling]

258
00:10:53,825 --> 00:10:54,654
- Sophie?

259
00:10:56,241 --> 00:10:57,898
- Marcia Wade.

260
00:10:57,933 --> 00:10:59,693
- Oh my gosh.

261
00:10:59,728 --> 00:11:01,143
What's it been 15 years?

262
00:11:01,177 --> 00:11:04,974
- You look the same if that's
possible.

263
00:11:05,009 --> 00:11:07,011
- Well you look healthy.

264
00:11:10,255 --> 00:11:11,705
Tell me this isn't yours.

265
00:11:11,740 --> 00:11:13,880
- Yeah he looks just like Dave.

266
00:11:13,914 --> 00:11:15,088
My other two are other there.

267
00:11:15,122 --> 00:11:16,537
- Mom, Mom!

268
00:11:16,572 --> 00:11:17,987
- Get your rat nest hairdo out
of my face!

269
00:11:18,022 --> 00:11:18,850
- Mom!

270
00:11:20,783 --> 00:11:23,406
- Kids, you ever think about
them?

271
00:11:23,441 --> 00:11:24,649
- Well let's just say the men I
date,

272
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:27,238
we're not spending a lot of
time thinking about babies.

273
00:11:27,272 --> 00:11:29,102
[laughing]

274
00:11:29,136 --> 00:11:31,000
I can't believe you and
Dave are still together.

275
00:11:31,035 --> 00:11:32,381
- Yeah.

276
00:11:32,415 --> 00:11:34,728
- God we used to have
so much fun in school.

277
00:11:34,763 --> 00:11:36,316
- [Sophie] I know.

278
00:11:36,350 --> 00:11:37,973
- You know, we should
get together for a drink.

279
00:11:38,007 --> 00:11:38,974
Catch up properly.

280
00:11:39,008 --> 00:11:40,803
- Yeah, you still at Coltrane
and Brock?

281
00:11:40,838 --> 00:11:42,529
- It's Wade, Coltrane and Brock.

282
00:11:42,563 --> 00:11:44,117
I took the whole thing over.

283
00:11:44,151 --> 00:11:44,945
[baby screaming and crying]

284
00:11:44,980 --> 00:11:46,533
- Oh well.

285
00:11:46,567 --> 00:11:47,810
- You'd better call.

286
00:11:47,845 --> 00:11:49,432
Martinis.

287
00:11:49,467 --> 00:11:51,434
- Not gonna happen.

288
00:11:51,469 --> 00:11:52,297
Here's your binky.

289
00:11:52,332 --> 00:11:53,782
Nikki, please.

290
00:11:53,816 --> 00:11:55,715
[baby crying]

291
00:11:55,749 --> 00:11:57,682
Oh that's good.

292
00:11:57,717 --> 00:11:59,960
Honey, it's time to see Santa.

293
00:11:59,995 --> 00:12:01,755
- He looks weird.

294
00:12:01,790 --> 00:12:04,171
- Uh well, no honey, come on.

295
00:12:06,139 --> 00:12:06,933
Over here.

296
00:12:06,967 --> 00:12:09,176
Santa is your friend.

297
00:12:09,211 --> 00:12:11,696
Don't you want to tell
Santa your special wish?

298
00:12:11,731 --> 00:12:12,904
- Uh uh.

299
00:12:12,939 --> 00:12:13,767
- No?

300
00:12:15,389 --> 00:12:16,390
Do you mind?

301
00:12:17,357 --> 00:12:18,151
- [Santa] Come on.

302
00:12:18,185 --> 00:12:20,394
- He doesn't bite, okay honey?

303
00:12:20,429 --> 00:12:22,189
See it's okay.

304
00:12:22,224 --> 00:12:23,570
- [Santa] Smile.

305
00:12:24,951 --> 00:12:26,642
[shutter clicking]

306
00:12:26,676 --> 00:12:30,542
And what does Mommy want for
Christmas.

307
00:12:30,577 --> 00:12:31,474
- Her life.

308
00:12:33,028 --> 00:12:35,962
[melancholy music]

309
00:12:39,897 --> 00:12:42,762
[twinkling music]

310
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:44,798
It's your turn now.

311
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:45,626
Come on.

312
00:12:45,661 --> 00:12:47,421
- [Santa] You must be Anna, huh?

313
00:12:47,456 --> 00:12:48,284
Come here.

314
00:12:50,597 --> 00:12:52,392
So what do you want for
Christmas.

315
00:12:52,426 --> 00:12:53,462
- A puppy.

316
00:12:53,496 --> 00:12:54,808
- [Santa] A puppy?

317
00:12:54,843 --> 00:12:56,396
What kind of puppy?

318
00:12:56,430 --> 00:12:58,260
- [Anna] A little snowball
puppy.

319
00:12:58,294 --> 00:12:59,502
- [Santa] Snowball puppy?

320
00:12:59,537 --> 00:13:00,331
- [Anna] Like that.

321
00:13:00,365 --> 00:13:01,573
- [Santa] Okay.

322
00:13:01,608 --> 00:13:03,506
Thanks a lot kid, Merry
Christmas.

323
00:13:03,541 --> 00:13:05,646
- [Anna] Merry Christmas.

324
00:13:09,409 --> 00:13:13,827
- Okay um, I've got 10
minutes to drive home

325
00:13:13,862 --> 00:13:16,554
and then three minutes to shower

326
00:13:16,588 --> 00:13:17,727
and then try on this dress.

327
00:13:17,762 --> 00:13:19,557
Oh my gosh I hope this dress
fits.

328
00:13:19,591 --> 00:13:20,489
I really do.

329
00:13:20,523 --> 00:13:23,630
Hey watch that, it's kinda hot
okay?

330
00:13:23,664 --> 00:13:26,806
- You know Santa said
I could have a puppy.

331
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:30,982
- You know Santa sometimes
brings other things.

332
00:13:31,017 --> 00:13:32,087
Come here.

333
00:13:32,121 --> 00:13:33,053
Santa brings other things

334
00:13:33,088 --> 00:13:34,261
that you might not have asked
for okay?

335
00:13:34,296 --> 00:13:35,573
- Maybe I should have asked for
a Mom

336
00:13:35,607 --> 00:13:36,608
who cares about my life.

337
00:13:36,643 --> 00:13:38,058
- You know you promised

338
00:13:38,093 --> 00:13:39,508
that if I bought you some hot
chocolate

339
00:13:39,542 --> 00:13:42,166
you'd stop complaining
for five minutes, alright?

340
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:42,994
- How can I?

341
00:13:43,029 --> 00:13:44,306
This is the worst day ever.

342
00:13:44,340 --> 00:13:45,134
- Agreed.

343
00:13:45,169 --> 00:13:47,585
Keys, keys, where are my keys?

344
00:13:47,619 --> 00:13:51,451
Oh god of randomly missing
things don't do this to me now.

345
00:13:51,485 --> 00:13:52,935
[keys jingling]

346
00:13:52,970 --> 00:13:54,661
Honey give me the keys.

347
00:13:54,695 --> 00:13:56,007
Anna, stop it.

348
00:13:56,042 --> 00:13:58,044
Just give me the keys.

349
00:13:58,078 --> 00:13:59,148
[keys jingling]

350
00:13:59,183 --> 00:14:00,943
Anna, stop it.

351
00:14:00,978 --> 00:14:02,772
Anna please.

352
00:14:02,807 --> 00:14:04,982
- Mom this is so boring
can we please just go?

353
00:14:05,016 --> 00:14:07,812
- I know, look, I would send
you to Venus

354
00:14:07,847 --> 00:14:09,607
and leave you there if I could,
alright?

355
00:14:09,641 --> 00:14:12,230
Anna what are you doing
with the hot chocolate?

356
00:14:12,265 --> 00:14:13,680
Stop that!

357
00:14:13,714 --> 00:14:15,026
[gasping]

358
00:14:15,061 --> 00:14:16,165
My new dress!

359
00:14:17,270 --> 00:14:18,167
Oh my gosh.

360
00:14:21,377 --> 00:14:23,207
How could you do that?

361
00:14:24,622 --> 00:14:27,280
How am I ever going to
get a dress that fits now.

362
00:14:27,314 --> 00:14:28,212
[kids yelling]

363
00:14:28,246 --> 00:14:29,282
[baby crying]

364
00:14:29,316 --> 00:14:30,662
- You shut up!

365
00:14:30,697 --> 00:14:33,182
[baby crying]

366
00:14:34,770 --> 00:14:37,600
[twinkling music]

367
00:14:40,224 --> 00:14:41,052
Shut up!

368
00:14:42,605 --> 00:14:44,884
[thumping]

369
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:56,102
[groaning]

370
00:14:59,657 --> 00:15:00,761
- Where am I?

371
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:04,731
What?

372
00:15:08,804 --> 00:15:10,875
The furniture department?

373
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:13,636
Or am I being punked?

374
00:15:14,672 --> 00:15:18,124
[TV actor speaking Spanish]

375
00:15:18,158 --> 00:15:21,092
By Pablo Escobar's mother.

376
00:15:21,127 --> 00:15:24,578
[voice speaking Spanish]

377
00:15:44,564 --> 00:15:46,048
- Slut, Margareta!

378
00:15:47,808 --> 00:15:49,949
[gasping]

379
00:15:52,192 --> 00:15:56,024
Your lobster cobb is
almost ready Miss Sophie.

380
00:15:57,232 --> 00:15:59,579
- I'm sorry did I scare you?

381
00:16:01,753 --> 00:16:03,203
- Are you okay?

382
00:16:03,238 --> 00:16:04,929
You don't look so good.

383
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:07,725
I told you, you're working too
hard.

384
00:16:07,759 --> 00:16:10,141
I make you a nice herbal tea.

385
00:16:11,073 --> 00:16:14,007
- This is definitely not my
life.

386
00:16:14,042 --> 00:16:15,353
- Okay, martini.

387
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:18,011
- It's a dream, right?

388
00:16:18,046 --> 00:16:18,874
It's a dream.

389
00:16:18,908 --> 00:16:20,289
Woo it's a dream.

390
00:16:21,221 --> 00:16:22,050
Of course.

391
00:16:31,266 --> 00:16:33,993
An amazing gravity defying
dream.

392
00:16:41,724 --> 00:16:45,728
[water gently splashing]

393
00:16:45,763 --> 00:16:50,078
Maybe I died and went off
to real estate heaven.

394
00:16:50,112 --> 00:16:51,424
[laughing]

395
00:16:51,458 --> 00:16:52,804
Hello!

396
00:16:52,839 --> 00:16:54,944
- [Santa] Well well it's you
again.

397
00:16:54,979 --> 00:16:58,672
- Aren't you that Santa from
the mall?

398
00:16:58,707 --> 00:17:01,123
- How do you like your present?

399
00:17:01,158 --> 00:17:02,124
- Kidnapping and hair
extensions.

400
00:17:02,159 --> 00:17:03,677
Very funny.

401
00:17:03,712 --> 00:17:05,748
- Oh I gave you more than that
sweetheart.

402
00:17:05,783 --> 00:17:08,096
I gave you a whole new life.

403
00:17:09,097 --> 00:17:10,374
- You did this?

404
00:17:11,202 --> 00:17:12,617
It isn't real.

405
00:17:12,652 --> 00:17:13,653
I'm dreaming.

406
00:17:13,687 --> 00:17:15,034
I'm sleeping.

407
00:17:15,068 --> 00:17:16,380
This is a dream.

408
00:17:17,898 --> 00:17:18,727
Obviously.

409
00:17:25,389 --> 00:17:27,563
[gasping]

410
00:17:28,702 --> 00:17:30,083
Aren't I?

411
00:17:30,118 --> 00:17:30,946
- Nope.

412
00:17:33,224 --> 00:17:34,294
- Get away from me.

413
00:17:34,329 --> 00:17:36,917
- Listen lady, I'm just
trying to do my job here.

414
00:17:36,952 --> 00:17:37,780
- And what kind of job is that?

415
00:17:37,815 --> 00:17:39,334
Where are my kids?

416
00:17:39,368 --> 00:17:40,162
Do you have my kids?

417
00:17:40,197 --> 00:17:41,025
Where are my kids?

418
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:42,751
- Whoa whoa just relax.

419
00:17:42,785 --> 00:17:45,857
Your kids are fine, such as
they are.

420
00:17:45,892 --> 00:17:47,894
- Okay what is that supposed to
mean?

421
00:17:47,928 --> 00:17:50,138
- I was sent here to help.

422
00:17:50,172 --> 00:17:52,485
And myself incidentally.

423
00:17:52,519 --> 00:17:54,694
I got into a bit of trouble on
my last job

424
00:17:54,728 --> 00:17:58,215
trying to make business
associates disappear.

425
00:17:58,249 --> 00:18:01,563
See the thing is I wound up
dead too.

426
00:18:01,597 --> 00:18:04,635
Bad boy, I know, but then
this opportunity came up

427
00:18:04,669 --> 00:18:07,016
to kind of make things right.

428
00:18:07,051 --> 00:18:09,088
- Oh really and how is it
right that I'm standing here

429
00:18:09,122 --> 00:18:11,607
half naked in the back yard of
a McMansion

430
00:18:11,642 --> 00:18:14,714
I don't recognize with
a pool cleaning Santa

431
00:18:14,748 --> 00:18:15,991
who claims he's dead.

432
00:18:16,025 --> 00:18:19,236
- You see once a year,
the big guy outsources.

433
00:18:19,270 --> 00:18:21,548
Hires a few schmucks to pick up
the slack,

434
00:18:21,583 --> 00:18:23,964
make a few wishes come true.

435
00:18:23,999 --> 00:18:26,726
So if I get this right,
I'll be enjoying my

436
00:18:26,760 --> 00:18:30,074
dearly departed Ma's
meatballs by New Years.

437
00:18:30,109 --> 00:18:34,492
- So you're dead and you need
me to help you get to heaven.

438
00:18:34,527 --> 00:18:35,942
Could this be any more cliche.

439
00:18:35,976 --> 00:18:39,118
- Look, from the minute
I saw you in the mall

440
00:18:39,152 --> 00:18:41,568
I knew you was a desperate
woman.

441
00:18:41,603 --> 00:18:44,157
And you needed your wish to
come true.

442
00:18:44,192 --> 00:18:47,402
Come on, could this be any
more like what you dreamed of?

443
00:18:47,436 --> 00:18:51,544
Perfect house, perfect life,
perfect uh...

444
00:18:51,578 --> 00:18:54,340
- Look I don't have time for
perfect.

445
00:18:54,374 --> 00:18:58,171
I have shopping to finish,
an office party not to enjoy,

446
00:18:58,206 --> 00:19:00,656
Christmas dinner for 23 and a
husband

447
00:19:00,691 --> 00:19:03,003
I still haven't finished
yelling at yet.

448
00:19:03,038 --> 00:19:04,108
[laughing]

449
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:05,661
- It's good you haven't
lost your sense of humor.

450
00:19:05,696 --> 00:19:07,491
You know I had this client in
Chicago,

451
00:19:07,525 --> 00:19:10,045
he went absolutely postal
when I turned his Ma

452
00:19:10,079 --> 00:19:12,185
into Joey Ramone.

453
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:13,082
[laughing]

454
00:19:13,117 --> 00:19:15,257
- Okay I'm going home now.

455
00:19:16,569 --> 00:19:17,363
[sighing]

456
00:19:17,397 --> 00:19:19,123
[gasping]

457
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:20,159
Would you just stop that?

458
00:19:20,193 --> 00:19:22,091
Okay I have to go home.

459
00:19:23,955 --> 00:19:25,612
- They're not there Sophie.

460
00:19:25,647 --> 00:19:26,786
- What do you mean they're not
there.

461
00:19:26,820 --> 00:19:29,271
You can't just make an entire
person's life disappear

462
00:19:29,306 --> 00:19:30,583
just like that.

463
00:19:30,617 --> 00:19:32,136
- I can and I did.

464
00:19:33,275 --> 00:19:34,414
- Well then bring them back.

465
00:19:34,449 --> 00:19:35,622
It's time for dinner.

466
00:19:35,657 --> 00:19:36,865
I need money for a taxi.

467
00:19:36,899 --> 00:19:37,969
Do you have any?

468
00:19:38,004 --> 00:19:40,662
Or is there a coach made
out of a pumpkin outside?

469
00:19:40,696 --> 00:19:41,801
- No see that's the thing.

470
00:19:41,835 --> 00:19:45,908
I'm still working the kinks
out of my return policy.

471
00:19:45,943 --> 00:19:47,496
- What is that supposed to mean?

472
00:19:47,531 --> 00:19:50,223
- That is for you to figure out.

473
00:19:50,258 --> 00:19:51,259
Otherwise...

474
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:53,502
- Otherwise what?

475
00:19:53,537 --> 00:19:56,160
- This one could be final sale.

476
00:19:58,852 --> 00:20:01,786
- You mean I could be stuck
like this?

477
00:20:01,821 --> 00:20:05,065
My entire family could be gone
forever?

478
00:20:06,446 --> 00:20:07,447
- Afraid so.

479
00:20:08,310 --> 00:20:10,416
- You can't do that.

480
00:20:10,450 --> 00:20:13,073
- Sure I can, I'm Santa Clause.

481
00:20:17,319 --> 00:20:18,907
- No, that's crazy.

482
00:20:26,121 --> 00:20:26,949
Look...

483
00:20:28,641 --> 00:20:30,815
[gasping]

484
00:20:33,646 --> 00:20:34,716
[phone buttons beeping]

485
00:20:34,750 --> 00:20:35,958
Please be there Dave.

486
00:20:35,993 --> 00:20:39,134
Honey, please be there, please
be there, please be there.

487
00:20:39,168 --> 00:20:40,169
- [Recorded Phone Voice]
The number you have reached

488
00:20:40,204 --> 00:20:42,102
is no longer in service.

489
00:20:42,137 --> 00:20:43,725
- No.

490
00:20:43,759 --> 00:20:45,140
No!

491
00:20:45,174 --> 00:20:47,280
[crying]

492
00:20:50,318 --> 00:20:52,423
Not that can't be me.

493
00:20:52,458 --> 00:20:53,459
Anna, Annie!

494
00:20:56,910 --> 00:20:57,842
Dave!

495
00:20:57,877 --> 00:20:59,603
Dave are you up here?

496
00:21:01,743 --> 00:21:02,571
Annie!

497
00:21:04,746 --> 00:21:05,574
Nikki!

498
00:21:13,168 --> 00:21:13,996
Anybody?

499
00:21:26,285 --> 00:21:27,078
My babies.

500
00:21:29,909 --> 00:21:32,083
[gasping]

501
00:21:48,307 --> 00:21:50,964
[keys jingling]

502
00:22:00,802 --> 00:22:03,701
[melancholy music]

503
00:22:10,777 --> 00:22:11,571
[knocking]

504
00:22:11,606 --> 00:22:13,193
Dave!

505
00:22:13,228 --> 00:22:14,402
[knocking]

506
00:22:14,436 --> 00:22:15,334
Dave honey!

507
00:22:15,368 --> 00:22:16,369
Nikki!

508
00:22:16,404 --> 00:22:17,370
Anybody home?

509
00:22:17,405 --> 00:22:18,958
It's me Mom!

510
00:22:18,992 --> 00:22:20,200
[knocking]

511
00:22:20,235 --> 00:22:21,374
It's me Mommy!

512
00:22:21,409 --> 00:22:22,479
Mommy's home.

513
00:22:24,343 --> 00:22:28,554
- If you're looking for the
O'Brians they're not home.

514
00:22:28,588 --> 00:22:31,453
- Barbara I am so glad to see
you.

515
00:22:34,491 --> 00:22:35,837
- Do I know you?

516
00:22:37,079 --> 00:22:37,977
- Yes of course you know me.

517
00:22:38,011 --> 00:22:39,910
I'm the flaky Mom from the PTA.

518
00:22:39,944 --> 00:22:43,396
I forgot to return the
bicycle pump last Spring.

519
00:22:43,431 --> 00:22:46,848
Barbara, I live next door to
you.

520
00:22:46,882 --> 00:22:48,539
My daughter Nikki and your
daughter have been friends

521
00:22:48,574 --> 00:22:50,921
since kindergarten, come on.

522
00:22:52,198 --> 00:22:55,063
- I'm sorry I don't know a
Nikki either,

523
00:22:55,097 --> 00:22:59,274
and as long as I can remember
the O'Brians live here.

524
00:22:59,308 --> 00:23:01,380
All nine of them.

525
00:23:01,414 --> 00:23:03,243
Do you need some help?

526
00:23:04,348 --> 00:23:06,730
- No, I'll just be going now.

527
00:23:18,293 --> 00:23:21,192
- Somebody's husband is in
trouble.

528
00:23:27,992 --> 00:23:30,719
[water dripping]

529
00:23:33,481 --> 00:23:35,621
[sighing]

530
00:23:38,002 --> 00:23:42,179
- It's only temporary so
I might as well enjoy it.

531
00:23:46,252 --> 00:23:49,082
[bubbles popping]

532
00:23:55,641 --> 00:23:56,469
Wow!

533
00:24:01,957 --> 00:24:04,546
[upbeat music]

534
00:24:08,447 --> 00:24:10,587
Oh my gosh, I am so tired.

535
00:24:23,876 --> 00:24:26,119
[laughing]

536
00:24:35,508 --> 00:24:37,648
