[joyful Christmas music]

1574
01:16:05,975 --> 01:16:08,529
[gasping]

1575
01:16:08,564 --> 01:16:10,980
Oh my god I'm still here.

1576
01:16:11,014 --> 01:16:13,154
That was supposed to be a magic
kiss.

1577
01:16:13,189 --> 01:16:15,363
I did everything you told me to
do.

1578
01:16:15,398 --> 01:16:17,538
I went back to the beginning
and the beginning is Dave

1579
01:16:17,573 --> 01:16:19,540
and I'm still here.

1580
01:16:19,575 --> 01:16:20,403
Oh god.

1581
01:16:20,437 --> 01:16:21,542
- Sophie what are you doing?

1582
01:16:21,577 --> 01:16:22,819
- Don't you see it didn't work.

1583
01:16:22,854 --> 01:16:24,683
I have to go back and
find that stupid Santa.

1584
01:16:24,718 --> 01:16:26,202
- No, no isn't it enough
that I'm willing to

1585
01:16:26,236 --> 01:16:27,721
go through this with you again.

1586
01:16:27,755 --> 01:16:28,998
I mean come on you don't have
to go on

1587
01:16:29,032 --> 01:16:30,827
with this charade, okay.

1588
01:16:30,862 --> 01:16:32,380
You won, you got me.

1589
01:16:32,415 --> 01:16:33,623
I'm yours.

1590
01:16:33,658 --> 01:16:35,418
So enough with the fairy tales.

1591
01:16:35,452 --> 01:16:37,144
- It's not a fairy tale Dave.

1592
01:16:37,178 --> 01:16:40,147
It's my life, it's your
life, it's our kids' life.

1593
01:16:40,181 --> 01:16:42,390
- Sophie, please don't go in
there.

1594
01:16:42,425 --> 01:16:44,634
Stay with me please.

1595
01:16:44,669 --> 01:16:46,602
- I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

1596
01:16:47,913 --> 01:16:50,260
Let me in, let me in please!

1597
01:16:51,296 --> 01:16:53,125
Oh god, I have to try.

1598
01:16:57,233 --> 01:16:58,752
I know there's a back door.

1599
01:16:58,786 --> 01:17:00,305
Dave, wait for me.

1600
01:17:07,726 --> 01:17:08,589
Santa!

1601
01:17:09,832 --> 01:17:11,523
Santa please, Santa!

1602
01:17:14,284 --> 01:17:15,113
Santa!

1603
01:17:18,634 --> 01:17:19,462
Oh god.

1604
01:17:21,567 --> 01:17:22,396
Santa.

1605
01:17:26,020 --> 01:17:26,849
No.

1606
01:17:30,404 --> 01:17:31,232
No, no.

1607
01:17:32,682 --> 01:17:34,822
[sobbing]

1608
01:17:59,744 --> 01:18:04,610
- So I got you the tree
and presents for children,

1609
01:18:04,645 --> 01:18:06,095
whoever they are.

1610
01:18:09,132 --> 01:18:12,860
- Thank you Sylvia, no really,
than you.

1611
01:18:12,895 --> 01:18:15,725
- You owe me 78 bucks and
I want time and a half

1612
01:18:15,760 --> 01:18:17,934
for working Christmas Eve.

1613
01:18:19,108 --> 01:18:21,179
- Wow, that's fair, you deserve
that.

1614
01:18:21,213 --> 01:18:24,009
And something a lot more.

1615
01:18:24,044 --> 01:18:24,838
Here.

1616
01:18:24,872 --> 01:18:26,840
- I have keys.

1617
01:18:26,874 --> 01:18:28,565
- No, for the house.

1618
01:18:30,153 --> 01:18:32,604
I want you to have it.

1619
01:18:32,638 --> 01:18:35,124
- You going to take pills or
put your head in the oven?

1620
01:18:35,158 --> 01:18:36,228
- No I'm not.

1621
01:18:38,886 --> 01:18:41,061
- I'll be out tomorrow.

1622
01:18:41,095 --> 01:18:43,373
I want you to have it.

1623
01:18:43,408 --> 01:18:45,513
It's not really my style.

1624
01:18:52,935 --> 01:18:53,763
- I know.

1625
01:19:09,192 --> 01:19:11,367
[sighing]

1626
01:19:20,100 --> 01:19:23,034
[melancholy music]

1627
01:19:35,184 --> 01:19:36,012
- Aw.

1628
01:19:40,810 --> 01:19:43,468
[bells chiming]

1629
01:19:48,956 --> 01:19:51,648
- You're busy later, right Mom?

1630
01:19:51,683 --> 01:19:54,030
But it's for school.

1631
01:19:54,065 --> 01:19:56,619
You're busy later, right Mom?

1632
01:19:56,653 --> 01:20:00,485
Maybe I should have asked for
a Mom who cares about my life.

1633
01:20:00,519 --> 01:20:01,451
- Oh Nikki.

1634
01:20:02,763 --> 01:20:04,592
Oh I forgot your play.

1635
01:20:10,564 --> 01:20:12,290
- How you holdin' up?

1636
01:20:13,878 --> 01:20:16,570
- My whole life I've been so
worried

1637
01:20:16,604 --> 01:20:19,228
about accomplishing everything,
you know,

1638
01:20:19,262 --> 01:20:21,920
being the best, being in charge,

1639
01:20:22,887 --> 01:20:23,888
being right.

1640
01:20:25,199 --> 01:20:28,927
I've been so wrapped up in my
own race to I don't know where

1641
01:20:30,860 --> 01:20:34,795
I'm missing the stuff that
matters along the way.

1642
01:20:34,830 --> 01:20:38,488
The things I should
have taken time to enjoy

1643
01:20:40,076 --> 01:20:41,975
like kissing my husband

1644
01:20:44,425 --> 01:20:47,428
and really listening to Anna
sing.

1645
01:20:47,463 --> 01:20:49,741
Those little morning snuggles
with JJ

1646
01:20:49,775 --> 01:20:53,918
and little Nikki, that play
was so important to her

1647
01:20:55,609 --> 01:20:58,336
and she was too proud to tell
me.

1648
01:20:59,716 --> 01:21:02,202
Oh, how could I let it happen?

1649
01:21:03,755 --> 01:21:05,274
How could I get so busy

1650
01:21:05,308 --> 01:21:08,484
that I'm actually missing my
own life?

1651
01:21:13,075 --> 01:21:15,767
I thought I wasn't doing enough,

1652
01:21:16,733 --> 01:21:19,391
but Dave had me all figured out.

1653
01:21:21,221 --> 01:21:25,950
My problem has always been
trying to do too much.

1654
01:21:25,984 --> 01:21:27,572
- Balance is important.

1655
01:21:27,606 --> 01:21:28,711
- Yeah it is.

1656
01:21:31,783 --> 01:21:34,406
But it's too late now, huh?

1657
01:21:34,441 --> 01:21:37,340
[melancholy music]

1658
01:21:39,964 --> 01:21:41,172
What?

1659
01:21:41,206 --> 01:21:44,347
- Well you see I just got back
from a quick run to Vegas.

1660
01:21:44,382 --> 01:21:47,488
This librarian who had a thing
for the Cirque du Soleil,

1661
01:21:47,523 --> 01:21:49,421
you know the dirty one?

1662
01:21:50,284 --> 01:21:54,392
You think I'm giving up this
easy on my Ma's meatballs?

1663
01:21:54,426 --> 01:21:57,913
I'm still running on Vegas
time, so this watch says

1664
01:21:57,947 --> 01:22:01,951
we still got 10 minutes
to get you back home.

1665
01:22:01,986 --> 01:22:02,952
[gasping]

1666
01:22:02,987 --> 01:22:05,748
What do you want for Christmas,
Sophie?

1667
01:22:05,782 --> 01:22:08,440
[bells ringing]

1668
01:22:34,294 --> 01:22:37,918
- All I want for
Christmas is my life back.

1669
01:22:43,510 --> 01:22:46,237
[ethereal music]

1670
01:22:51,518 --> 01:22:52,346
I'm home.

1671
01:22:53,520 --> 01:22:55,418
[gasping]

1672
01:22:55,453 --> 01:22:56,281
I'm home.

1673
01:22:58,697 --> 01:23:00,596
Is anybody here?

1674
01:23:00,630 --> 01:23:01,769
I'm up.

1675
01:23:01,804 --> 01:23:03,979
- Mom's awake, Mom's awake!

1676
01:23:04,013 --> 01:23:08,155
- Honey, you have no idea
how glad I am to see you.

1677
01:23:09,053 --> 01:23:10,744
- We got a puppy from Santa.

1678
01:23:10,778 --> 01:23:12,815
Mom did you see our new puppy?

1679
01:23:12,849 --> 01:23:14,023
[puppy barking]

1680
01:23:14,058 --> 01:23:16,129
His name's Joey Ramone.

1681
01:23:16,163 --> 01:23:17,337
Joey, come on.

1682
01:23:18,786 --> 01:23:20,616
- Joey Ramone?

1683
01:23:20,650 --> 01:23:21,548
- Joey!

1684
01:23:21,582 --> 01:23:23,343
[laughing]

1685
01:23:23,377 --> 01:23:24,896
- He's so cute.

1686
01:23:24,930 --> 01:23:25,897
Honey where's Daddy?

1687
01:23:25,931 --> 01:23:27,657
- He's in the kitchen.

1688
01:23:27,692 --> 01:23:28,486
- Lets go.

1689
01:23:28,520 --> 01:23:31,282
[child laughing]

1690
01:23:32,628 --> 01:23:34,043
Honey!

1691
01:23:34,078 --> 01:23:36,080
- What are you doing up?

1692
01:23:37,426 --> 01:23:39,152
You are supposed to be resting.

1693
01:23:39,186 --> 01:23:41,775
You had a fever of 103.

1694
01:23:41,809 --> 01:23:43,949
- Oh my god how long was I out?

1695
01:23:43,984 --> 01:23:45,020
- A few days.

1696
01:23:45,054 --> 01:23:47,919
The doctor said it was acute
exhaustion.

1697
01:23:47,953 --> 01:23:49,610
- Wait, wait, what about
the presents and the food

1698
01:23:49,645 --> 01:23:50,646
and is my mother here--

1699
01:23:50,680 --> 01:23:51,957
- Just don't worry about it.

1700
01:23:51,992 --> 01:23:53,890
We're doing a pot luck, we've
got everything under control.

1701
01:23:53,925 --> 01:23:55,858
Your sister's going to
bring those yams with the

1702
01:23:55,892 --> 01:23:58,447
disgusting little marshmallow
things.

1703
01:23:58,481 --> 01:24:00,380
So listen, hey hey hey.

1704
01:24:01,657 --> 01:24:02,968
Go back to bed.

1705
01:24:03,003 --> 01:24:07,076
I've got, I'm in charge, so go
on you little control freak.

1706
01:24:07,111 --> 01:24:08,457
- Oh my gosh go!

1707
01:24:10,010 --> 01:24:11,425
- No no no no no.

1708
01:24:15,291 --> 01:24:16,672
- Hey honey.

1709
01:24:16,706 --> 01:24:18,432
- Hi Mom, are you feeling
better?

1710
01:24:18,467 --> 01:24:20,158
- Yeah I am.

1711
01:24:20,193 --> 01:24:22,229
Look I'm really sorry
about missing your play.

1712
01:24:22,264 --> 01:24:23,230
- It's okay.

1713
01:24:23,265 --> 01:24:25,094
It was just some stupid drama
class thing.

1714
01:24:25,129 --> 01:24:26,130
- No it wasn't.

1715
01:24:26,164 --> 01:24:27,510
It was important and I
should have been there.

1716
01:24:27,545 --> 01:24:29,098
- It's okay Mom, really.

1717
01:24:29,133 --> 01:24:31,307
- Look, things are going to
be different from now on.

1718
01:24:31,342 --> 01:24:32,619
I promise.

1719
01:24:32,653 --> 01:24:34,069
I'm still going to forget a few
things

1720
01:24:34,103 --> 01:24:35,311
and I'm going to need your help
with that

1721
01:24:35,346 --> 01:24:38,280
but I'm going to try
to just, I don't know,

1722
01:24:38,314 --> 01:24:42,939
just be here with you and
not wish my life away.

1723
01:24:42,974 --> 01:24:45,321
- Mom, you are here.

1724
01:24:45,356 --> 01:24:46,426
- Yeah, I am.

1725
01:24:47,910 --> 01:24:50,637
- Okay who wants crispy
pancakes?

1726
01:24:51,569 --> 01:24:53,467
- Why do they smell like
meatballs?

1727
01:24:53,502 --> 01:24:56,401
Mom, do you smell meatballs?

1728
01:24:56,436 --> 01:24:58,507
- Yeah I smell meatballs.

1729
01:24:59,473 --> 01:25:01,613
- Mom, promise me you're not
going to be

1730
01:25:01,648 --> 01:25:04,133
one of those parents who quits
their job to stay at home

1731
01:25:04,168 --> 01:25:07,447
and then spends all their
time bugging their kids.

1732
01:25:07,481 --> 01:25:08,482
- I promise.

1733
01:25:13,453 --> 01:25:14,902
- No no no don't.

1734
01:25:23,635 --> 01:25:25,810
My 50 million dollar deal.

1735
01:25:28,675 --> 01:25:32,023
Margaret Lasky just gave that
land away.

1736
01:25:34,198 --> 01:25:37,373
- Well, take this up the
mountain Bob.

1737
01:25:39,099 --> 01:25:40,238
- Resignation?

1738
01:25:43,759 --> 01:25:46,313
[upbeat music]

1739
01:25:51,284 --> 01:25:53,217
- So how did Bob react?

1740
01:25:53,251 --> 01:25:54,735
- It was magnificent.

1741
01:25:54,770 --> 01:25:56,599
- I'm looking slimmer
these days don't you think?

1742
01:25:56,634 --> 01:25:58,187
- So who's our first client?

1743
01:25:58,222 --> 01:26:02,364
- Margareta DeSouza, some
big time real estate mogul.

1744
01:26:14,652 --> 01:26:18,103
[upbeat Christmas music]

